summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from C. M. Sheafe and L. Dora Gow, Administrators of the Estate of John H. Nagle, deceased, to the City of Seattle, dated the 23rd day of November, 1897, to all of Blocks thirty-six (36), Twenty nine (29) and Twenty (20); and the East half of Block Thirty five (35); the East half of Block Thirty (30); and the East half of Block nineteen (19), all in John H. Nagle's Second Addition to the City of Seattle, as shown by the recorded plat thereof now on file in the Auditor's Office of King County, Washington.
